{
  "stem": "8.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I remember when I was little and we heard about Hitler, how we used to make plans how to get to rid of him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Little children, how we would trick him into going someplace where he would fall down and break his neck and all kinds of things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Now, we heard most of the news through the shul where my, my father went.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Because our newspapers really did not report everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "They were always censored.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And, I remember being scared that there will be another war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "I remember my parents talking about it, and I remember praying-- I was very religious as a little child-- praying that there should not be another war.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "My parents were so busy that they did not have a lot of time for me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "I spent most of my time with the maid, who took care of me because my parents were so busy.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And, she was not Jewish and somehow, we worked out a, a wonderful relationship with my-- she even learned how to say the prayers with me in Hebrew, so that she really substituted my mother.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "My two brothers went to Chedar and in the later years, in the late '30s, early '40s, they could not go alone anymore because they were stoned by the Gentile kids.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "So that my-- the maid had to accompany them, and they often came back with, with bloody heads after they were hit.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "There were many nights when our business, which had an iron, like, shutter from the outside, which we closed every night that people were banging on them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And, ask them, open you-- open it up, you dirty Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And I remember how scared I was and seeing my mother grabbing a kitchen knife and going toward the door.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
